George Bundi bagged Sh1 million during the eighth Lotto draw.The father of two said he has been playing Lotto since January 2016 without any luck, so it was a huge surprise for him when he received a call informing him that he had literally become a millionaire overnight. The 50-year-old resident of Nyeri Countyis the latest millionaire after his ticket numbers 43, 44, 28, 25, 13, 8 (7) were picked in the draw.The potato farmer is ecstatic about his win, which he says shall be a big boost to his farming business, especially having switched from coffee to potatoes four years ago. Bundi, 50, said he will use the money to purchase a plot of land and build is own house, which has been his life-time dream.